# Microsoft Teams Integration Configuration
# 
# These variables enable NAVI to sync Teams messages into conversational memory.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Register an app in Azure AD (https://portal.azure.com/#blade/Microsoft_AAD_RegisteredApps)
# 2. Note the following from "Overview" page:
#    - Application (client) ID
#    - Directory (tenant) ID
# 3. Create a client secret under "Certificates & secrets"
# 4. Add Microsoft Graph API permissions under "API permissions":
#    - ChannelMessage.Read.All (Application permission)
#    - Group.Read.All (Application permission)
# 5. Grant admin consent for the permissions
# 6. Copy these values to your .env file

# Azure AD tenant (directory) ID
AEP_MS_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id-here

# Application (client) ID
AEP_MS_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here

# Client secret value (not the secret ID)
AEP_MS_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here

# Optional: List of team names to monitor (comma-separated)
# If not set, the sync endpoint requires explicit team names in requests
# AEP_MS_TEAMS=Engineering,Product,Design
